doc:CloudDeployment schema:description "Process of retrieving and selecting manuscripts for systematic review, including risk of bias and validity threats assessment."@en , "Metric M1: Provides comprehensive state of the art aligned with SLR and identifies knowledge gaps to justify the study."@en , "Metric M4: Manuscript published under an open license."@en , "Criteria applied to narrow down articles for systematic review, including temporal, linguistic, publisher alignment, paywall, and citation thresholds."@en ;
	a schema:Review ;
	schema:description "PRISMA statement emphasizing the need to describe search and selection process results, potentially using a flow diagram."@en .
doc:MLWorkflowOrchestration schema:datePublished "2026-04-20"^^xsd:date ;
	a schema:Review ;
	schema:description "A systematic review focusing on MLOps and AIOps concepts from 2018 onward, including selection criteria and quality metrics for included articles."@en .
doc:CloudDeployment schema:description "Metric M2: Research validated against at least one use case aligned with SLR objectives."@en , "Metric M3: Number of research questions tightly coupled with the manuscript, ranging from 0 to 5."@en , "Classification of articles based on quality scores: deficient (0-2), sufficient (3-4), good (5-6), very good (7-8), excellent (9-10)."@en , "Metrics used to evaluate included articles, including alignment with SLR goals, use case validation, research questions, open license, publication type, JIF quartile, and citation count."@en , "Inclusion criteria for articles: published from 2018 onward, English language, aligned with MLOps/AIOps topics, open access or accessible via subscriptions, and meeting citation thresholds based on publication year."@en , "Metric M5: Publication type categorized as journal or other."@en , "Minimum citation thresholds applied: 4 for 2018, 3 for 2019, 2 for 2020, 1 for 2021; no threshold for 2022 onward."@en , "Articles published from 2018 onward are included; newer articles (2022 onward) are not filtered by citation count to preserve freshness."@en , "Metric M6: Manuscript published in a journal in the first JIF quartile."@en , "Quality score assigned to each article based on metrics, ranging from 0 (deficient) to 10 (excellent)."@en , "Exclusion criteria for articles: non-English, retracted, misaligned publishers, paywalled, and failing citation thresholds based on publication year."@en , "Metric M7: Citation count of the manuscript, ranging from 0 to 3."@en .
